com.kuka.connectivity.fri
Class FRISession

java.lang.Object
  com.kuka.connectivity.fri.FRISession

public final class FRISession
extends java.lang.Object

Class to open the FRI channel from the KUKA controller to a remote system.

The typical workflow for FRI is:

  1. Create the configuration
    FRIConfiguration configuration = FRIConfiguration.createRemoteConfiguration(lbr_iiwa_7_R800_1, "192.168.42.40");

    Note: Minimum required information for opening the FRI channel:
    • The (robot) device reference on the KUKA Controller
    • The remote host address
  2. Open the FRI channel
    FRISession mySession = new FRISession(configuration);
  3. use the channel
  4. when done - close it
    mySession.close();

See Also:
FRIConfiguration.createRemoteConfiguration(Device,String), FRISession(FRIConfiguration)

await

public void await(long timeout,
                  java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit timeUnit)
           throws java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException
Blocks the calling thread until the FRI connection quality state of the FRISession equals GOOD or EXCELLENT or the timeout has elapsed. If the FRI connection quality state is already GOOD or EXCELLENT when called, this method returns immediately.

Parameters:
timeout - The maximum time the calling thread is blocked.
timeUnit - The unit of the timeout.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if time out is null
java.lang.IllegalStateException - if FRI-Session is not open
java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException - if time out elapsed before the FRI connection quality state equals GOOD or EXCELLENT
